63
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:52,572
No, it's not like that.

64
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:58,077
<i>Ms. Matsuyama is</i>

65
00:02:58,144 --> 00:03:01,781
<i>my mother's editor of 20 years.</i>

66
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,449
<i>But because of the recession,</i>

67
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,885
<i>Saneisha asked for employees to</i>
<i>retire early,</i>

68
00:03:05,952 --> 00:03:06,953
<i>and she volunteered.</i>

69
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,521
<i>Today is her last day.</i>

70
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,193
It's been so long, Editor-in-Chief!

71
00:03:13,259 --> 00:03:16,229
I'm sorry it's been so long, star writer!

72
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:18,198
As expected of
the queen of romance novels.

73
00:03:18,264 --> 00:03:20,266
What a beautiful home you have.

74
00:03:21,301 --> 00:03:22,235
What's wrong?

75
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:24,571
Is that a bean jelly from Tatsuya?

76
00:03:24,637 --> 00:03:25,705
